# LiteRadar tracker rev 200104 by miktim@mail.ru

Run demo (the wonderful ideal world): 
  https://miktim.github.io/literadar/tracker?mode=demo,nowatch&track=30:0.5

Run tracker:
  https://miktim.github.io/literadar/tracker?watch=180:30:t&track=30:.5

URL query parameters (optional, see defaults in tracker.js):
  mode  (mode=watch)
    watch   - watch your location;
    nowatch - disable watching your own location;
    demo    - run demo.

  watch (watch=180:30:t)
    watch_timeout(sec):watch_maximumAge(sec):watch_high_accuracy(t/f)
    See: https://w3c.github.io/geolocation-api/#dom-positionoptions

  track (track=30:0.5)
    minimal_track_segment_length(meters):multiplier(>=0)
    track_segment_length = max(minimal_track_segment_length,
       minimal_track_segment_length x speed(meters per second) x multiplier)

  ws (ws=undefined) for embedded solutions
    WebSocket server address:port
    Note: WebSocket protocol depends on page protocol: http - ws,  https - wss.
    Example: ws=localhost:10090
